Types of pointer : 
a. null pointer : which have null values means a pointer that doesnt point to any valid memory location

b. wild pointer : pointer that hasn't been initialized it points to a random memory locations;

c.void pointer  : void pointer is point to any data types .

d. dangling pointer : pointer to a memory lcation that has been freed or deallocated 

e. function pointer : pointer to point a function instead of a variable 

f. Pointer to pointer (double pointer ) : pointer that points to another pointer .

g. constant pointer  cannot change thier address it is holding 

h. pointer to constant a pointer to value that an not be chaned throught the pointer 

9. constant pointer to constant : both the pointer and the value it pointes to can not be changed 


